= Chapter 1

We can easily see from @bennett-sharpley that the Riemann hypothesis can be easily proven by the techniques used in interpolation of operators.

#theorem([Riemann])[
  The Riemman $zeta$ function defined as
  $ zeta(s) = sum_(n = 1)^infinity 1/(n^s) $
  has no non-trivial zeros outside of the line $"Re" z = 1/2$.
] <riemann>

#proof([of @riemann])[
  Easy exercise for the reader.
]
